Title: Community Tax Certificate and Permits Issuing on Digital Certificates Using Verifiable Credentials, Digital Wallet on a Blockchain as Payment Provision, and Machine Learning

Abstract

The present invention is directed towards an innovative and novel way of issuing community tax certificates and other relevant permits and clearances as digital certificates using verifiable credentials, digital wallet on a blockchain as payment provision, and machine learning

Background

Community tax certificates are necessary for several reasons including conducting business in a community, ensuring compliance with local tax and permit laws, and verifying entitlement to benefits. The current process of issuing community tax certificates and permits involves manual procedures that can be time-consuming and prone to errors. Furthermore, manual procedures require physical documents that can become lost, misplaced, or destroyed, leading to delays, complications, and potential consequences for businesses and individuals involved.

Claims

1. A system and method for issuing community tax certificates and permits as digital certificates using verifiable credentials, digital wallet on a blockchain as payment provision, and machine learning, said system and method comprising:
   a. A dashboard for registering businesses, submitting applications for community tax certificates and permits, and managing applications;
   b. A verification module for verifying business information, checking for existing community tax certificates and permits, and cross-verifying data with other sources;
   c. A machine learning module for analyzing business data, detecting patterns and anomalies, and identifying potential areas of fraudulent activities;
   d. A payment and transaction management module for securely processing payments, verifying transactions, and providing transaction histories;
   e. A blockchain-based digital wallet module for securely storing and managing digital certificates, keys, and other sensitive data;
   f. A messaging and notification module for communicating with businesses, sending automated messages and reminders, and providing status updates.

2. A method for issuing community tax certificates and permits as digital certificates using verifiable credentials, digital wallet on a blockchain as payment provision, and machine learning, said method comprising the steps of:
   a. Registering businesses using a dashboard;
   b. Submitting applications for community tax certificates and permits using the dashboard;
   c. Verifying business information using a verification module;
   d. Checking for existing community tax certificates and permits using the verification module;
   e. Cross-verifying data with other sources using the verification module;
   f. Analyzing business data using a machine learning module;
   g. Detecting patterns and anomalies using the machine learning module;
   h. Identifying potential areas of fraudulent activities using the machine learning module;
   i. Securely processing payments and verifying transactions using a payment and transaction management module;
   j. Securely storing and managing digital certificates, keys, and other sensitive data using a blockchain-based digital wallet module;
   k. Transmitting automated messages and reminders, and providing status updates using a messaging and notification module;
   l. Facilitating communication between businesses and the system using the messaging and notification module and the dashboard.

3. A system and method for issuing community tax certificates and permits as digital certificates using verifiable credentials, digital wallet on a blockchain as payment provision, and machine learning, said system and method comprising the system and method claims 1-2 above. 

